
Here is my suggestion.You don't need add a new config entry like: `kylin.query.asc-order-null-first-enable`. 

Looks like you can reuse existent config entry in `KylinConfigBase#getCalciteExtrasProperties` and remove the overwrite method `defaultNullCollation` of KECalciteConfig.  After that, you 
just need set "kylin.query.calcite.extras-props.defaultNullCollation=low/high/first/last" in kylin.properties .

@zznlime

After check, I have following commnets:

1. Looks like a lot of configuration entries is hard-coded in `MemcachedCacheConfig`, such as `timeout`, do they really not need be configured by kylin users?
2. Would you please add unit test for `CompositeMemcachedCache`? A good example is `QueryRedisCacheTest`. And I find a embedded-memcached in https://github.com/mwarc/embedded-memcached-spring.

@zznlime

Thanks for the suggestion! Have removed the config 'kylin.query.asc-order-null-first-enable', and reuse KylinConfigBase#getCalciteExtrasProperties for setting default null collation.

@hit-lacus
LGTM, I will merge it later.
